      • updateShoot

        public void updateShoot()
        Updates the elements currently stored in the easy level. It first updates the player/launcher movement. If the up key is pressed, the first element of the inventory is moved up to where the launcher is and canMove is set to true. The inventory will then be shifted to the left.
        Parameters:
        index - - int - Stores the index of the element at the location with row 10 and column 1.
        dart - - GameParticle - Stores the temporary element to be shot with.
        x - - int - Increments through for loop.
